
rkdebootstrap have following parameter:
--suite: debian version, default is buster(debian10)
--deb_arch: platform value(arm, armeb, armel, armhf, arm64), default value is arm64.
--base: will get minibase debian rootfs from services
--wifi: will download wifi relate package
--audio: will download audio relate package and copy relate config to debian rootfs
--clean: clean unnecessary file to reduce debian rootfs sizes, after enable it, if you
         want to use apt-get, need to run "apt-get update" first
--package: package debian rootfs to ext4 rootfs image

you can run command:
sudo rkdebootstrap --suite buster --deb_arch arm64 --base --wifi --audio --clean --package
to generate debian rootfs image

Script can detect fastest mirror to download the rootfs, but request PC install netselect-apt,
otherwise it will use http://ftp.cn.debian.org/debian as default mirror.
